    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your<strong> green lentils</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>drained green lentils</strong> to the onion with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan (save the rest for later!) with the<strong> sliced mushrooms</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong>,<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min or until thickened to a bolognese-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong> lentil & mushroom pie mix</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of<strong> flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff</strong> <strong>pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin</strong> and cut into 1 rectangle per person</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pastry</strong> to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), then score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p><p>Crimp the borders with a fork and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until puffed up and golden \u2013 this is your<strong> pie lid</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pastry is almost cooked, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded kale </strong>with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and a small splash of<strong> cold water</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until tender \u2013 these are your<strong> garlicky greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lentil-and-mushroom-pie-with-garlicky-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pie lid</strong> over the <strong>lentil & mushroom pie mix</strong> with the<strong> garlicky greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
